<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-06T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7008: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-07T12:00:00+08:00">June 7,
                                1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The transfer of Yu Hsueh-chung from his post as chairman of Hopei
                            Province to that of Bandit Suppression Commander for the Szechuan,
                            Shansi and Kansu border is officially confirmed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>